text: Carlos Antonio Carrillo (24 December 1783 – 23 February 1852) was a California politician, military officer, and ranchero. He served as governor of Mexican Alta California 1837-1838. Carlos died at Santa Bárbara and was buried in the mission cemetery February 26, 1852. Category:1783 births Category:1852 deaths Category:Politicians from California
